        <div n="Y48A18N1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HE furniture that best doth please</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-2"> St. Patrick's dean, good sir, are these:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-3"> The knife and fork with which I eat;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-4"> And next the pot that boils the meat;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-5"> The next to be preferr'd, I think,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-6"> Is the glass in which I drink;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-7"> The shelves on which my books I keep;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-8"> And the bed on which I sleep;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-9"> An antique elbow-chair between,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-10"> Big enough to hold the dean;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-11"> And the stove that gives delight</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-12"> In the cold bleak wintry night;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-13"> To these we add a thing below,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-14"> More for use reserved than show:</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-15"> These are what the dean do please;</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-Y48A18N1-line-16"> All superfluous are but these.Y48A18N1   </l></lg></div>
